Revision history for PDL-Graphics-Cairo

{{NEXT}}
    - Driver unification: macOS native display is now the giza_server
      backend ('gs'). _default_backend() returns 'gs' on darwin (falling
      back to 'gnuplot' only when giza_server is neither running nor
      installed). Driver::GS->_available() added for that probe.
    - Driver::OSX / pdlcairo_viewer are DEPRECATED. They are no longer
      built or installed (Makefile.PL postamble/EXE_FILES disabled); the
      source is kept under src/osx/ for reversibility. Constructing an OSX
      driver now warns once. 'osx' remains selectable (PDLCAIRO_BACKEND=osx
      or backend => 'osx') as a legacy fallback.
    - PGPLOT layer: the /osx device (legacy) and the new /gs, /gw devices
      now display through giza_server (Driver::GS).
    - wait_all() is a harmless no-op under the gs path (empty OSX queue;
      no warning), so existing nowait+wait_all scripts keep working.
    - examples/regress_gs.pl: regression harness for the unified path
      (matplotlib-style, PGPLOT-style, show_interactive, wait_all no-op,
      gnuplot fallback).

0.01  (first appear in Github, 2026-05-18)
    - Initial release
    - Backend: Cairo + Pango (PNG / PDF / SVG output)
    - Plot types: line, scatter, bar, barh, hist, errorbar,
                  fill_between, step, stem, imshow, contourf,
                  pie, axhline, axvline, axvspan, axhspan,
                  text, annotate, boxplot, violinplot, qqplot,
                  hist_kde, heatmap, stackplot, eventplot, quiver
    - Axes: autoscale, grid, legend, colorbar, twinx
    - Scale: linear, log (semilog-x/y, log-log)
    - Colormap: viridis, plasma, jet, hot, cool, gray, RdBu
    - Subplot grid: subplots(rows, cols)
    - Unicode text via Pango
    - PGPLOT compatibility layer (PDL::Graphics::Cairo::PGPLOT)
        - 53 functions fully implemented
        - cpgbox / pgbox with A/N/S/T/B/C/G/V options
        - cpgenv negative-up Y axis (ymin > ymax)
        - PGPLOT_BACKGROUND=black support
        - Multi-panel column-major layout (negative nxsub)
        - cpgmtxt multi-line title (disp parameter)
        - cpgsave / cpgunsa attribute stack
        - cpgrnd / cpgrnge / cpgnumb (untested)
    - Interactive display via gnuplot (aqua / wxt / x11)
